<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-272-014 </DOCNO><DOCID>08 187 148</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Publishing Systems  Feb 12 1990 v19 n10p27(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mycro-Tek acquires Mac-based system.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mycro-Tek Inc. (products).andO;Topic:     NewspapersTurnkey SystemsDistribution Agreements.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Mycro-Tek has acquired the exclusive worldwide distribution rights to aMacintosh-based newspaper system it will call the Mycro-Comp 2500.andP;  Developedby Steve Rockwell, of Coming Publishing, the system has been in use inproducing three newspapers and two shoppers, plus some other work.andM;It includes software for file management, display ad composition, wirecapture, classified costing, accounts receivable, billing and invoicing.andO;Text files are sent to Quark Xpress for pagination and output to PostScriptimagesetters.andM;The system win be demonstrated at the Seybold Seminars in March and initialdeliveries are scheduled for the first quarter.andM;Mycro-Tek's existing newspaper editorial and classified system runs on PCterminals linked to a Mycro-Comp system.andP;  Its AdWriter for display adcomposition runs on a Macintosh.andO;</TEXT></DOC>